contentrichtext.text: '''Diarmuid''' may refer to: ;Given name *[[Diarmuid Ua Duibhne]] *[[Diarmuid Martin]] (born 1945, Roman Catholic Archbishop of Dublin and Primate of Ireland *[[Diarmuid Gavin]] (born 1964) ], Irish garden designer and television personality *[[Diarmuid O'Sullivan]] (born 1978), Irish sportsperson *[[Diarmuid O'Scannlain]] (born 1937) American judge on the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit *[[Diarmuid Hegarty (Griffith College)]], president of Griffith College Dublin *[[Diarmuid Connolly]] (born1987), Dublin Gaelic football and Hurling player *[[Diarmuid O'Carroll]] (born 1987), Irish professional footballer *[[Diarmuid Lynch]] (1878 – 1950), member of the Irish Republican Brotherhood and Sinn Féin member *[[Diarmuid Murphy]] (born 1975), Irish sportsperson. *[[Diarmuid Lawrence]] (born 1947), British television director *[[Diarmuid Lyng]] (born 1981), Irish sportsperson *[[Diarmuid O'Neill]] (1969 - 1996), volunteer in the Provisional Irish Republican Army *[[Diarmuid O'Hegarty]], Irish revolutionary and civil servant *[[Diarmuid Kirwan]], Irish hurling referee *[[Diarmuid Downs]] (born 1922), British automotive engineer *[[Diarmuid Wilson]] (born 1965), Irish Fianna Fáil politician and member of Seanad Éireann ;Fictional name *[[Prince Diarmuid]]; Irish folk tale protagonist ;Other *[[Diarmuid Ua Duibhne]] *[[The Pursuit of Diarmuid and Gráinne]] ==See also== *[[Diarmid (disambiguation)]] *[[Diarmait (disambiguation)]] *[[Dermot (disambiguation)]] {{disambig}}
